Thousands of people have been taking part in protests in Beirut, following the catastrophic blast  that killed hundreds of people and injured many others. The Lebanese government resigned on Monday. We want to hear how people are feeling following the explosion. In what ways have you been affected? How do you feel authorities have dealt with the situation? What do you think should be done now? You can get in touch by filling in the form below, anonymously if you wish – only the Guardian has access to your contributions. One of our journalists will be in contact for publication before we publish, so please do leave contact details. If you’re having trouble using the form, click here. Read terms of service here.